article.headline: Utah Valley St. 71, Furman 66
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Ryan Toolson scored 26 points, eight of which were free throws in the final 1:26, to give Utah Valley State a 71-66 win over Furman in the consolation bracket of the Gossner Foods Holiday Classic on Friday night. Jordan Brady also scored 14 for the Wolverines (5-8) and Richard Troyer added 10 points and pulled down a game-high 10 rebounds. Justin Dehm scored 22 to lead Furman (0-10). Dehm shot 5-of-9 from behind the 3-point line. Utah Valley State took a 42-41 lead with 9:45 left in the second half when Toolson hit a 20-foot shot. Moments later, Brady got a steal and a breakaway dunk to give the Wolverines a 48-43 lead. The teams then traded leads before Toolson gave the Wolverines a 58-55 edge on a jump shot with 2:39 remaining. Furman led most of the first half, which ended in a 30-23 edge for the Paladins.
